the enchanted barn is a 1919 silent film , directed by david smith , starring bessie love and j. frank glendon . the script was written by kathryn reed , based on the eponymous novel by grace livingston hill lutz . bessie love was familiar with the source novel , and was instrumental in optioning it for this film . the film is considered lost . on its release , the film was shown with the comedy short soapsuds and sapheads .